---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Analyze Cloudflare Logs Locally - GigaSieve Guide" description="Extract Ray-IDs, status codes, and top URLs from Cloudflare logs without uploading.">
    <section class="container mx-auto px-4 py-12 max-w-3xl">
        <nav class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-6">
            <a href="/guides" class="hover:text-cyan-400">Guides</a>
            <span class="mx-2">/</span>
            <span class="text-slate-400">Analyze Cloudflare Logs Locally</span>
        </nav>

        <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-slate-200 mb-4">Analyze Cloudflare Logs Locally</h1>
        <p class="text-slate-400 mb-8">
            Cloudflare logs are huge and sensitive. Use local analysis to understand traffic and errors without sending data to a server.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 p-6 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-300 mb-4">What you can learn</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-400 text-sm">
                <li>Top URLs and endpoints</li>
                <li>4xx/5xx error spikes</li>
                <li>Ray-ID tracing for incidents</li>
                <li>Top IPs or user agents</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 p-6 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-300 mb-4">Step-by-step</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-slate-400 text-sm">
                <li>Download a log sample from Cloudflare.</li>
                <li>Open it in GigaSieve /app.</li>
                <li>Run the Ray-ID and status code recipes.</li>
                <li>Check hourly error spikes and top URIs.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 rounded-xl border border-slate-800 p-6 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-300 mb-4">Privacy note</h2>
            <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm">Logs stay on your device. GigaSieve never uploads your files.</p>
        </div>

        <a href="/app" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-gradient-to-r from-emerald-500 to-cyan-500 text-white font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg mb-8">
            Try GigaSieve ->
        </a>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-300 mb-4">Related</h2>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <a href="/guides/analyze-nginx-access-log" class="bg-slate-900 hover:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-800">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-300">Analyze nginx Access Log</h3>
            </a>
            <a href="/guides/remove-pii-from-logs" class="bg-slate-900 hover:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-800">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-300">Remove PII from Logs</h3>
            </a>
            <a href="/recipes/logs/cloudflare-ray-id" class="bg-slate-900 hover:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-800">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-300">Cloudflare Ray-ID Extract</h3>
            </a>
            <a href="/recipes/logs/status-by-hour" class="bg-slate-900 hover:bg-slate-800 rounded-xl p-4 border border-slate-800">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-300">Status Codes by Hour</h3>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>
